org.dummycreator
Class ClassBindings

java.lang.Object
  org.dummycreator.ClassBindings

public class ClassBindings
extends java.lang.Object

Stores a list of classes / interfaces and their associated deferred types. This list is used to tell DummyCreator which specific implementation it should use to product new dummy instances for a certain type.

Classes can be used as deferred types, but the following deferred types are allowed:

  • Class references: add(Class, Class)
  • methods with a return type: add(Class, Method)
  • constructors: add(Class, Constructor)
  • instance objects: add(Class, Object)
Examples are:
  • List -> ArrayList
  • List -> LinkedList
  • Integer -> 4443 (which is autoboxed to an Integer)
  • Foo -> FooFactory.class.getMethod('createFoo')
  • Apple -> Apple.class.getConstructor(String.class)
